    <PrimAttribute name="timeTill2ndResource" id="4064cbba-370b-40ff-9c9a-eccaaad0efc2">
        <precision>12</precision>
        <scaleFactor>2</scaleFactor>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Decimal"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>This is used to determine if to add an extra block of chargeable time.

The wharf has two resources used for charging berthage.

Typically they are set for one 24 hour block and additional 6 hours blocks.

timeTill2ndResource is set to be about 1.5 hours this means that if berthage is for 25 hours we do not 
add any 6 hour blocks, however if berthage is for 26 hours then we will add 1 X 6 hour block.

In addition once we are adding 6 hours blocks 'timeTill2ndResource' is used again to determine when to 
round up and add 1 extra 6 hours block or not i.e. If berthage is for 49 hours there will be 1 X 24 hour block 
and 4  X 6 hour blocks, this leaves 1 hour which is ignored, however if the berthage is for 50 hours there will 
be 1 X 24 hour block and 5 X 6 hour blocks.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
